      "description": "Presenting a driver-focused E92 M3, powered by the high-induction S65 4.0L V8 engine. This unit features a flat torque curve and a blistering 8,400 RPM redline, facilitated by eight individual throttle bodies and a sophisticated ionic current knock-sensing system. The 6-speed manual transmission delivers tactile shifts, sending power through a GKN-sourced variable M differential. Maintenance is up to date, including the critical rod bearing service and throttle actuator replacements. The vehicle exhibits excellent lateral dynamics thanks to the Electronic Damper Control (EDC) and a low polar moment of inertia aided by the CFRP roof panel. Though the front fascia shows minor stone chips consistent with spirited use, the mechanical integrity and subframe mounting points are robust, making this an ideal specimen for the discerning purist.",
